<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <title>FAQs</title>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@4.0.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-Gn5384xqQ1aoWXA+058RXPxPg6fy4IWvTNh0E263XmFcJlSAwiGgFAW/dAiS6JXm" crossorigin="anonymous">
  
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.4.1/css/bootstrap.min.css">

  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Allura&family=Poppins:wght@300&family=Yellowtail&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

  
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/jquery@3.6.0/dist/jquery.slim.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@4.6.1/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>

</head>
<body>

<%- include("#homeheader.ejs"); %>

<div class="container mt-3">
  <h3>FAQs</h3>
  <div id="accordion">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header">
        <a class="card-link" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseOne">
          Question: Can Donors claim money while giving dry-wastes to the receivers?
        </a>
      </div>
      <div id="collapseOne" class="collapse show" data-parent="#accordion">
        <div class="card-body">
          Answer: No. The purpose of this web application is to donate the dry-wastes to the Receivers without any money. However this matter is between the Donors and the Receivers.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header">
        <a class="collapsed card-link" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseTwo">
         Question: What are the things will be considered as dry-waste?
        </a>
      </div>
      <div id="collapseTwo" class="collapse" data-parent="#accordion">
        <div class="card-body">
         Answer: Any waste except wet-waste (kitchen waste, used diaper etc). All kind of dry-wastes can be recycled. The most common dry-wastes are plastic bottles, plastic wrappers, single use plastic carry bags, glass bottles, metal cans, paper, paper-box, thermocol items, electronics waste and any kind of plastic, glass, metal wastes. Please see the lists in the "Recyclable Items" tab.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-header">
        <a class="collapsed card-link" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseThree">
          Question: How much dry-waste can be given at a time?
        </a>
      </div>
      <div id="collapseThree" class="collapse" data-parent="#accordion">
        <div class="card-body">
          Answer: As much as you like. It is recommended to store all types of dry-wastes for a month at home and then donate to the receiver. It is better for Receivers to collect more dry-wastes at a time, instead of collecting multiple times with less amount.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>